1. To clone a project form github
    -> go to the file manager and select where you want to clone the project
    open cmt ,do execute this command : git clone (git hub url)
2. command: git pull
     ->to get changes from remote
3. to push my changes to remote
     firstly we need to add file or files which we want to move to remote
     -> add comment: git add (file name) or to add all files :git add *
     secondly we need to commit the changes by using the following comment: git commit -m "(your commit message)"
     finally use git push